PSWD
Version 2
Author: David Waring
Email: dave@davidwaring.net

PSWD is a pseudo-random password generator that creates
site-specific passwords from a domain and master password
(along with additional options).  It uses a hashing 
algorithm to create the password so when the same
domain and master password are given, the program
will generate the same password.



        Password Generator        
Version: 2.0
Written by: David Waring (c) 2011
http://www.davidwaring.net/

USAGE: pswd [options] [arguments] [domain]

OPTIONS:
  -c, --caps : 
    toggle the use of caps
    DEFAULT = 1
  -d, --domain <arg> : *REQUIRED
    specify the domain
  -h, --help :
    display this help message
  -n, --length <arg> :
    specify the length of the generated password
    DEFAULT = 14
  -p, --password <arg> : *REQUIRED
    specify the master password
    DEFAULT = <saved>
  -q, --quiet :
    hide the generated password (only copy it to clipboard)
  -s, --symbols :
    toggle the use of symbols
  -t, --symchars <arg>
    specify the string of characters to use as symbols
    DEFAULT = !@$%^*()_-+=<,>.?/
  -v, --verbose :
    turn on debugging messages
    THIS WILL REVEAL YOUR MASTER PASSWORD
  -x, --passes <arg> :
    specify the number of times the initial key is hashed
    DEFAULT = 250